WEBVTT

1
00:00:50.166 --> 00:00:51.500
<i>Where do I start?</i>

2
00:00:51.666 --> 00:00:55.166
<i>Well. I guess what I really</i>
<i>want to say is.</i>

3
00:00:55.333 --> 00:00:59.416
<i>everything I am is because of</i>
<i>where I come from.</i>

4
00:01:01.916 --> 00:01:06.166
<i>Eternia.</i>
<i>a world of endless beauty.</i>

5
00:01:07.166 --> 00:01:09.000
<i>All that stuff</i>
<i>that only exists</i>

6
00:01:09.125 --> 00:01:11.500
<i>in legends</i>
<i>and bedtime stories.</i>

7
00:01:11.666 --> 00:01:15.208
<i>On Eternia.</i>
<i>that stuff is real.</i>

8
00:01:16.416 --> 00:01:19.625
<i>Griffins. dragons.</i>
<i>talking tigers.</i>

9
00:01:20.208 --> 00:01:22.791
<i>enchanted forests.</i>
<i>burning deserts.</i>

10
00:01:22.916 --> 00:01:25.041
<i>islands in the sky.</i>
<i>You name it.</i>

11
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:28.166
<i>I... I swear I'm not high.</i>

12
00:01:30.083 --> 00:01:34.000
<i>And then</i>
<i>we've got Castle Grayskull.</i>

13
00:01:34.708 --> 00:01:36.083
<i>My father once told me</i>

14
00:01:36.208 --> 00:01:39.666
<i>that Eternia is the beating</i>
<i>heart of the cosmos.</i>

15
00:01:40.125 --> 00:01:43.333
<i>And Grayskull</i>
<i>is the heart of that heart.</i>

16
00:01:43.666 --> 00:01:47.583
<i>So. I... I guess the. uh...</i>
<i>the heart of the heart</i>

17
00:01:47.750 --> 00:01:52.125
<i>of. uh. the heart</i>
<i>is the Power of Grayskull.</i>

18
00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:56.916
<i>They say it can make a man</i>
<i>as mighty as a god.</i>

19
00:01:58.166 --> 00:02:02.000
<i>To keep it safe. the Power</i>
<i>was bound within a vessel.</i>

20
00:02:02.416 --> 00:02:07.416
<i>An ancient sword they called</i>
<i>the Sword of Power.</i>

21
00:02:08.083 --> 00:02:10.041
<i>Yeah. I know.</i>

22
00:02:10.166 --> 00:02:11.583
<i>but that's what</i>
<i>they went with.</i>

23
00:02:12.791 --> 00:02:16.541
<i>Legend said that when Eternia</i>
<i>was in its greatest need.</i>

24
00:02:16.708 --> 00:02:19.833
<i>a hero would step forth</i>
<i>and wield the Sword.</i>

25
00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.916
<i>and. you know. use it...</i>

26
00:02:24.708 --> 00:02:26.083
<i>awesomely.</i>

27
00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:29.458
<i>Until that day. it was locked</i>
<i>away within the castle</i>

28
00:02:29.625 --> 00:02:32.541
<i>under the watchful eye</i>
<i>of the Sorceress.</i>

29
00:02:32.708 --> 00:02:35.541
<i>who was wise. and ancient.</i>

30
00:02:35.708 --> 00:02:37.625
<i>and a little scary.</i>
<i>to be honest.</i>

31
00:02:37.750 --> 00:02:40.500
<i>But she's cool.</i>
<i>She's... She's cool.</i>

32
00:02:41.666 --> 00:02:44.166
<i>For hundreds of years.</i>
<i>Grayskull has remained</i>

33
00:02:44.291 --> 00:02:46.666
<i>under the protection</i>
<i>of my ancestors.</i>

34
00:02:47.125 --> 00:02:48.666
<i>See. I come from</i>

35
00:02:48.791 --> 00:02:51.708
<i>a pretty impressive lineage</i>
<i>of mighty heroes.</i>

36
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:56.791
<i>Noble. strong. fearless.</i>

37
00:02:56.958 --> 00:03:00.041
But. Mom.
I don't want to fight.

38
00:03:00.583 --> 00:03:03.000
Everyone's bigger than me
and stronger.

39
00:03:03.166 --> 00:03:05.083
And I have poor
hand-eye coordination.

40
00:03:05.250 --> 00:03:07.833
- Nonsense! Who told you that?
- Cringer.

41
00:03:08.208 --> 00:03:11.000
It's true. He's the smallest
and the weakest.

42
00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:14.416
It's a miracle he hasn't
broken any bones or died.

43
00:03:15.333 --> 00:03:17.125
So. what should
the prince be doing

44
00:03:17.250 --> 00:03:19.083
instead of arms training. hmm?

45
00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:22.250
I don't know. maybe hanging
out and playing with Cringer.

46
00:03:22.416 --> 00:03:25.125
You go. I'll find a ball
of yarn and I'm good.

47
00:03:25.291 --> 00:03:26.708
You're zero help. you know.

48
00:03:27.458 --> 00:03:29.000
Do I have to go?

49
00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:32.958
Arms training. Now.

50
00:03:41.083 --> 00:03:45.416
Listen up.
future finest of Eternos.

51
00:03:46.166 --> 00:03:49.833
There are no statues
of losers.

52
00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:53.083
no streets
named after cowards.

53
00:03:53.250 --> 00:03:57.666
and there are no parades
for doing your best.

54
00:03:57.833 --> 00:04:01.916
This ground. that palace.
your entire lives

55
00:04:02.083 --> 00:04:03.750
are built on the backs
of men and women

56
00:04:03.875 --> 00:04:06.833
who have won the fight.

57
00:04:07.416 --> 00:04:09.458
And as your
king's Man-At-Arms.

58
00:04:09.583 --> 00:04:12.375
you can bet
I won a lot of fights.

59
00:04:12.541 --> 00:04:14.875
That's why we're all here.

60
00:04:15.041 --> 00:04:18.416
I saved your mom
and dad's asses.

61
00:04:18.583 --> 00:04:20.250
I saved your neighbor's asses.

62
00:04:20.375 --> 00:04:22.583
I saved your neighbor's
mom and dad's asses.

63
00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:24.166
That is a lot of asses.

64
00:04:24.291 --> 00:04:26.916
You know what. the point is
I fought for you.

65
00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:30.833
and now you are going to fight
for me with keen reflexes.

66
00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:35.500
sure aim. and glorious muscle.

67
00:04:36.375 --> 00:04:37.583
And this.

68
00:04:37.750 --> 00:04:39.500
Anybody know what it is?

69
00:04:39.875 --> 00:04:41.000
It's a stick.

70
00:04:45.708 --> 00:04:47.958
Thank you
for stating the obvious.

71
00:04:49.291 --> 00:04:50.291
Anybody else?

72
00:04:50.958 --> 00:04:51.958
Teela?

73
00:04:52.541 --> 00:04:53.666
Your arms.

74
00:04:53.875 --> 00:04:55.041
That's my girl!

75
00:04:56.625 --> 00:05:01.625
These are your arms.
They are an extension of you.

76
00:05:01.791 --> 00:05:03.833
All right. partner up. Arm up.

77
00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.750
I want to see big.
shiny bruises.

78
00:05:06.916 --> 00:05:11.083
I want to see bloody noses.
I want to see chipped teeth.

79
00:05:11.250 --> 00:05:13.208
Okay. let's go.
Anchor your weight.

80
00:05:13.333 --> 00:05:14.541
Hey. Dian.
Do you want to...

81
00:05:14.666 --> 00:05:16.208
If this was real.
you just died twice.

82
00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:19.875
- Adam.
- Eyes up!

83
00:05:20.041 --> 00:05:21.583
You got to look him in the eye
when you smash him

84
00:05:21.708 --> 00:05:23.041
in the face.

85
00:05:23.416 --> 00:05:25.416
Parry or next time
it'll be harder.

86
00:05:25.791 --> 00:05:27.333
Maybe we could just sit down
and talk about this?

87
00:05:27.500 --> 00:05:32.083
Hey. Adam. Adam.
Just do what you can. okay?

88
00:05:32.708 --> 00:05:35.041
Yeah. Teela.

89
00:05:36.041 --> 00:05:37.416
Aah!

90
00:05:38.416 --> 00:05:39.708
What kind of a friend are you?

91
00:05:39.875 --> 00:05:41.333
The kind
that's going to beat you.

92
00:05:54.541 --> 00:05:55.541
Duncan.

93
00:05:58.791 --> 00:06:01.541
How do you think
our novices are faring?

94
00:06:02.708 --> 00:06:05.250
They're a fine
and diligent bunch. Sire.

95
00:06:06.041 --> 00:06:07.041
All of them?

96
00:06:07.208 --> 00:06:08.750
No dancing. Adam.

97
00:06:09.375 --> 00:06:10.375
Mm-hmm.

98
00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:12.750
- Come on.
- Hit me! Hit me!

99
00:06:12.958 --> 00:06:14.708
He's making
a fool out of himself.

100
00:06:14.875 --> 00:06:17.791
I promised to make him
into a man. and I will.

101
00:06:17.958 --> 00:06:20.625
Yeah. But what kind of man?

102
00:06:20.791 --> 00:06:23.083
- Adam!
- Just hit me!

103
00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:27.500
Well. he did disarm her.

104
00:06:27.791 --> 00:06:30.250
That's not
how this works. old friend.

105
00:06:30.958 --> 00:06:32.625
I win! I win! I win!

106
00:06:33.708 --> 00:06:35.666
You're being silly.
Adam.

107
00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:40.000
Boy.

108
00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:45.000
Face me. With this.

109
00:06:48.458 --> 00:06:49.458
Well. pick it up.

110
00:06:55.916 --> 00:06:56.916
Now...

111
00:06:59.791 --> 00:07:01.333
defend yourself.

112
00:07:02.583 --> 00:07:04.500
Dad.

113
00:07:04.791 --> 00:07:05.791
Dad!

114
00:07:11.416 --> 00:07:14.125
This world
is no place for the weak.

115
00:07:14.541 --> 00:07:15.833
Yes. Dad.

116
00:07:16.666 --> 00:07:17.666
Now say it.

117
00:07:19.875 --> 00:07:23.416
This world
is no place for the weak.

118
00:07:24.250 --> 00:07:25.291
Hmm.

119
00:07:32.625 --> 00:07:34.458
Adam. Get up!

120
00:07:35.291 --> 00:07:36.291
Get up.

121
00:07:36.875 --> 00:07:38.041
When you fall.

122
00:07:39.416 --> 00:07:43.791
this is your chance
to stand tall. Okay?

123
00:07:45.041 --> 00:07:46.333
Now look strong.

124
00:07:46.500 --> 00:07:49.750
When he turns around.
he's going to see you.

125
00:07:49.916 --> 00:07:52.750
And you want to show him
you can take a hit.

126
00:07:53.833 --> 00:07:55.333
When he turns around.

127
00:07:55.458 --> 00:07:57.583
he's not going to see
a frightened little boy.

128
00:07:57.708 --> 00:07:59.250
He's going to see a man.

129
00:07:59.416 --> 00:08:00.625
What's he going to see?

130
00:08:01.083 --> 00:08:03.291
- A man.
- Good. Look.

131
00:08:03.625 --> 00:08:05.166
As soon as he turns around.

132
00:08:15.666 --> 00:08:16.791
Walk it off. lad.

133
00:08:24.166 --> 00:08:27.250
Show's over.
Back to work. Let's go.

134
00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:41.375
Adam.

135
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:42.500
What are you doing here?

136
00:08:42.666 --> 00:08:44.208
Following you.

137
00:08:44.583 --> 00:08:48.125
Yeah. well.
I came here to be alone. so...

138
00:08:48.291 --> 00:08:49.458
Don't be such a squink.

139
00:08:52.583 --> 00:08:54.750
I didn't think
you were weak. you know.

140
00:08:55.208 --> 00:08:57.208
Today at training.

141
00:08:58.125 --> 00:08:59.583
My dad did.

142
00:09:06.583 --> 00:09:10.083
Is that... the Sorceress?

143
00:09:12.500 --> 00:09:13.625
What is she looking at?

144
00:09:32.291 --> 00:09:34.250
King Randor.
we are under attack.

145
00:09:40.708 --> 00:09:42.416
I have this in hand. Sire.

146
00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:45.166
The Royal Guard
are trained for this.

147
00:10:41.708 --> 00:10:43.166
I promise.

148
00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:46.666
no harm will come to you
nor your family.

149
00:10:46.833 --> 00:10:49.500
I'll get you safely
to Grayskull. Guards!

150
00:10:50.875 --> 00:10:51.875
Hey. it's okay.

151
00:10:52.541 --> 00:10:53.541
Stay close.

152
00:10:55.541 --> 00:10:56.625
Teela! Come on.

153
00:10:56.791 --> 00:10:57.791
Dad...

154
00:10:58.416 --> 00:10:59.416
I'm scared.

155
00:10:59.833 --> 00:11:03.166
Who taught you that word?
Huh? Not me.

156
00:11:03.333 --> 00:11:05.125
It's going
to be all right. pet.

157
00:11:05.541 --> 00:11:08.000
Whatever happens.
as long as I'm here.

158
00:11:08.125 --> 00:11:10.416
you have nothing to fear.
All right?

159
00:11:11.666 --> 00:11:12.750
Come on. Come on.

160
00:11:22.958 --> 00:11:25.208
Now go! Go. go!

161
00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:28.750
There's too many of them.

162
00:11:28.875 --> 00:11:30.250
A big army
only means one thing.

163
00:11:32.916 --> 00:11:34.250
More targets.

164
00:11:53.250 --> 00:11:54.375
Go. go!

165
00:11:59.208 --> 00:12:00.375
Follow me.

166
00:12:01.541 --> 00:12:02.666
We're going this way.

167
00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.083
All right. just stay there.

168
00:12:43.083 --> 00:12:46.083
Weak little palace boys.

169
00:12:46.916 --> 00:12:49.500
Sire. go and don't stop.

170
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:52.375
Go. I'll settle this.

171
00:12:54.416 --> 00:12:56.083
Somebody wants to brawl.

172
00:13:06.708 --> 00:13:08.166
That's far enough.

173
00:14:17.250 --> 00:14:19.666
How dare
you come into my city!

174
00:14:19.791 --> 00:14:21.083
Don't you know
who you're messing with?

175
00:14:21.583 --> 00:14:23.083
Why don't you tell me.

176
00:14:23.250 --> 00:14:27.375
I am Duncan.
Commander of the Royal Guard.

177
00:14:32.125 --> 00:14:34.791
The King's goddamn
Man-At-Arms.

178
00:14:36.333 --> 00:14:37.750
And today...

179
00:14:37.875 --> 00:14:39.916
And today...

180
00:14:46.125 --> 00:14:47.333
You failed.

181
00:15:05.916 --> 00:15:08.416
Dad. Dad.

182
00:15:08.583 --> 00:15:12.333
Okay. come on. On your feet.
Get up. Come on. Please.

183
00:15:12.541 --> 00:15:13.583
Teela.

184
00:15:14.166 --> 00:15:15.916
I failed.

185
00:15:21.375 --> 00:15:22.375
Come on.

186
00:15:23.958 --> 00:15:25.625
Hold on.

187
00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:40.000
The reign of Randor

188
00:15:40.125 --> 00:15:42.666
comes to an end this night.

189
00:15:43.250 --> 00:15:45.208
You believed yourself
so strong.

190
00:15:45.333 --> 00:15:48.250
you stopped fearing
what lurked in the shadows.

191
00:15:49.291 --> 00:15:50.875
It was me.

192
00:15:52.666 --> 00:15:54.333
I lurked.

193
00:15:54.916 --> 00:15:59.083
In the deepest and darkest
corners of the universe.

194
00:15:59.208 --> 00:16:01.541
I lurked.

195
00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:04.583
But now
I step into the light...

196
00:16:06.166 --> 00:16:10.750
so you shall
look upon your downfall.

197
00:16:11.416 --> 00:16:13.000
Go. Don't look back.

198
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:17.750
Adam. don't worry. my boy.
I have you.

199
00:16:20.291 --> 00:16:21.875
Be strong. son.
I'll hold them.

200
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:23.000
Dad?

201
00:16:23.125 --> 00:16:25.500
Go!

202
00:16:27.291 --> 00:16:28.416
Dad!

203
00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:06.041
What will you do to me.
you fiend?

204
00:17:06.208 --> 00:17:08.916
I'm only going to cut off
your head.

205
00:17:17.833 --> 00:17:21.958
No matter my fate.
Eternos will never be yours.

206
00:17:22.125 --> 00:17:26.041
Your palace is nothing
but brick and glass.

207
00:17:26.208 --> 00:17:28.416
Your crown. a costume.

208
00:17:29.125 --> 00:17:30.208
Mm?

209
00:17:31.083 --> 00:17:33.708
No. I want the power
behind it.

210
00:17:35.958 --> 00:17:37.250
Evil-Lyn?

211
00:17:39.708 --> 00:17:41.166
Oh. Evil-Lyn.

212
00:17:41.500 --> 00:17:45.166
Well said. Lord Skeletor.
Poetry.

213
00:17:45.333 --> 00:17:47.583
Take him away.
His day is done.

214
00:17:48.833 --> 00:17:50.333
With a new dawn.

215
00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:53.916
Eternia shall witness my rise.

216
00:18:14.958 --> 00:18:17.250
-That's it. I finished.
-Of course. my Lord.

217
00:18:17.416 --> 00:18:18.583
When I raise my fist
like that.

218
00:18:18.708 --> 00:18:19.708
-I'm done.
-Yes.

219
00:18:19.833 --> 00:18:22.791
That is the crescendo!

220
00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:24.791
We'll know
for the future. my Lord.

221
00:18:32.958 --> 00:18:33.958
They're coming.

222
00:18:35.458 --> 00:18:36.625
Grayskull will fall.

223
00:18:36.791 --> 00:18:39.083
No. it will endure.

224
00:18:39.708 --> 00:18:41.250
Bring the Sword to me. child.

225
00:18:44.375 --> 00:18:45.833
Yes. Now hurry.

226
00:19:09.875 --> 00:19:11.833
You must
take the Sword somewhere safe.

227
00:19:12.625 --> 00:19:14.250
somewhere far away from here.

228
00:19:17.791 --> 00:19:20.166
Then let it be a place
they will never find him.

229
00:19:20.500 --> 00:19:21.625
My home.

230
00:19:29.875 --> 00:19:32.750
Adam. you be safe...

231
00:19:33.916 --> 00:19:36.083
and never forget
where you came from.

232
00:19:38.375 --> 00:19:40.416
That sword is mine.

233
00:19:43.375 --> 00:19:44.958
Be a good lad
and bring it to me.

234
00:19:45.125 --> 00:19:47.541
Don't you dare
come one step closer.

235
00:19:51.333 --> 00:19:52.333
Mom.

236
00:19:52.541 --> 00:19:55.166
Oh. darling. I dare.

237
00:19:55.541 --> 00:19:59.333
Do not lose the Sword.
It's your only way home.

238
00:20:00.416 --> 00:20:02.291
You carry the hope of Eternia.

239
00:20:03.458 --> 00:20:04.625
Now go!

240
00:20:15.416 --> 00:20:17.458
Go!

241
00:20:27.958 --> 00:20:29.666
No!

242
00:20:41.208 --> 00:20:44.625
<i>Anyway.</i>
<i>that's how I ended up in</i>

243
00:20:45.083 --> 00:20:46.625
Oklahoma City.

244
00:20:47.958 --> 00:20:49.708
What about you. Julie?

245
00:20:49.833 --> 00:20:51.583
Is your family
from around here?

246
00:20:53.583 --> 00:20:56.750
I'm sorry.
did you say "Skeletor"?

247
00:20:57.416 --> 00:20:59.416
Yeah. Yeah. I did.

248
00:20:59.583 --> 00:21:00.666
Yeah.

249
00:21:01.166 --> 00:21:04.208
Okay. um. I have to take this.

250
00:21:05.375 --> 00:21:07.250
You're ph... It didn't ring.

251
00:21:07.375 --> 00:21:09.125
No. I have to take it
and leave.

252
00:21:09.666 --> 00:21:12.083
Oh. okay. Julie. I'm...
I'm sorry.

253
00:21:12.458 --> 00:21:16.875
