Now!

512
00:41:57.750 --> 00:41:58.958
<i>Getting out of here now.</i>

513
00:42:07.291 --> 00:42:09.416
Hang on.
It's about to get weird.

514
00:42:09.791 --> 00:42:12.208
-Okay.
-Ship. fold space.

515
00:42:12.500 --> 00:42:14.125
<i>Folding space</i>
<i>and getting weird.</i>

516
00:42:40.166 --> 00:42:41.791
I can't believe it's you.

517
00:42:42.708 --> 00:42:44.083
Yeah.

518
00:42:44.791 --> 00:42:47.375
-It's me.
-You've gotten so big.

519
00:42:49.666 --> 00:42:50.833
As in you've aged.

520
00:42:52.541 --> 00:42:55.416
Well! You've aged well.
You've... You've grown older!

521
00:42:57.250 --> 00:42:58.958
And you haven't
changed at all.

522
00:42:59.833 --> 00:43:01.541
Well...

523
00:43:05.666 --> 00:43:07.666
Adam. you don't know
how bad it's been.

524
00:43:08.125 --> 00:43:11.666
I mean. everything changed
since you left.

525
00:43:11.833 --> 00:43:12.833
My parents?

526
00:43:15.500 --> 00:43:18.291
Skeletor took them
that night.

527
00:43:19.458 --> 00:43:22.208
and. um.
we never saw them again.

528
00:43:23.000 --> 00:43:25.375
<i>Arriving at Eternia</i>
<i>in ten.</i>

529
00:43:25.916 --> 00:43:29.541
<i>nine. eight. seven. six...</i>

530
00:43:29.666 --> 00:43:31.416
I can't believe
I'm finally home.

531
00:43:32.458 --> 00:43:34.583
I would manage
your expectations.

532
00:43:34.708 --> 00:43:36.875
<i>...two. one.</i>

533
00:43:48.291 --> 00:43:49.500
It's all gone.

534
00:43:53.666 --> 00:43:56.083
Skeletor
never wanted Eternos.

535
00:43:56.250 --> 00:43:58.666
He just didn't want
anyone else to have it.

536
00:43:59.916 --> 00:44:01.416
Why would he do this?

537
00:44:01.875 --> 00:44:03.333
Because he's bad.

538
00:44:05.416 --> 00:44:07.583
There's got to be
more to it than that.

539
00:44:09.041 --> 00:44:10.833
He has a skull for a face.

540
00:44:12.000 --> 00:44:13.625
We have to leave.

541
00:44:13.750 --> 00:44:15.916
It's too dangerous
to be out in the open.

542
00:45:08.958 --> 00:45:10.500
What are you looking at?

543
00:45:10.625 --> 00:45:11.916
Sorry. sir.

544
00:45:12.041 --> 00:45:13.875
I wasn't sure if you were
awake or not. my lord.

545
00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:16.375
Fetch my staff. swine.

546
00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:17.625
Yes. sir.

547
00:45:17.791 --> 00:45:19.583
Careful! If you drop it.

548
00:45:19.708 --> 00:45:21.875
I'll have you ground
into sausage meat.

549
00:45:22.000 --> 00:45:23.458
just like your mother.

550
00:45:26.416 --> 00:45:28.083
My lord. Skeletor...

551
00:45:29.958 --> 00:45:32.750
the beast has returned.

552
00:45:39.666 --> 00:45:42.750
Oh. vile
and villainous Skeletor.

553
00:45:43.125 --> 00:45:45.791
Sadistic Overlord of Evil...

554
00:45:45.958 --> 00:45:49.958
Oh. do shut up! On your knees.

555
00:45:52.875 --> 00:45:53.958
Lower.

556
00:45:54.083 --> 00:45:56.166
Lower.

557
00:45:57.916 --> 00:45:59.916
Lower.

558
00:46:00.541 --> 00:46:02.458
Tell me you have the Sword.

559
00:46:02.625 --> 00:46:05.500
I found it. my lord.
but the woman. Teela. took it.

560
00:46:05.625 --> 00:46:08.750
Please stop.
This really hurts. my lord.

561
00:46:09.208 --> 00:46:10.333
Teela?

562
00:46:10.458 --> 00:46:12.875
The whelp
of the King's Man-At-Arms.

563
00:46:13.000 --> 00:46:16.125
Intelligence reports her ship
flying recon over Eternos

564
00:46:16.250 --> 00:46:17.333
just this morning.

565
00:46:17.625 --> 00:46:19.250
Then the Sword is here.

566
00:46:19.416 --> 00:46:22.333
We must follow her
and see where she runs.

567
00:46:22.500 --> 00:46:24.583
That is already in hand.
my lord.

568
00:46:24.708 --> 00:46:25.708
Mm.

569
00:46:29.916 --> 00:46:31.208
Why are you still here?

570
00:46:31.333 --> 00:46:34.916
Bring me that sword.
you hirsute half-wit!

571
00:46:37.083 --> 00:46:40.750
What am I. Evil-Lyn?
Am I not mighty?

572
00:46:40.875 --> 00:46:44.750
My lord.
you are the mightiest.

573
00:46:44.875 --> 00:46:46.416
Have I not gone
out of my way

574
00:46:46.541 --> 00:46:47.875
to show
the people of Eternia

575
00:46:48.000 --> 00:46:51.125
that I am a just
and worthy ruler?

576
00:46:51.291 --> 00:46:54.041
You have killed thousands
of them to prove it.

577
00:46:54.208 --> 00:46:56.708
Oh. but what is it worth?

578
00:46:56.833 --> 00:46:58.916
My lord. if I may?

579
00:47:00.166 --> 00:47:02.666
You have already won.

580
00:47:02.833 --> 00:47:05.208
You have a vast army
at your command.

581
00:47:05.333 --> 00:47:09.208
Your Staff of Havoc.
your throne of bones.

582
00:47:09.333 --> 00:47:12.166
you have... me.

583
00:47:13.291 --> 00:47:15.583
Do you really need more?

584
00:47:15.750 --> 00:47:18.291
It can all be taken away.
Don't you see?

585
00:47:18.708 --> 00:47:20.208
My Staff can be taken away.

586
00:47:20.333 --> 00:47:22.125
You can be taken away.
All of it.

587
00:47:22.291 --> 00:47:25.541
And then. what am I?

588
00:47:25.833 --> 00:47:27.041
My lord. you are...

589
00:47:27.166 --> 00:47:28.666
Then I am nothing.

590
00:47:28.791 --> 00:47:30.625
As long as that sword

591
00:47:30.750 --> 00:47:32.875
remains
in someone else's hand.

592
00:47:33.041 --> 00:47:35.500
any power I have
is only temporary.

593
00:47:36.750 --> 00:47:38.625
I need more than impermanence.

594
00:47:39.500 --> 00:47:41.458
I am no mere king.

595
00:47:42.083 --> 00:47:43.500
I am a devil.

596
00:47:43.916 --> 00:47:46.583
but I mean to be a god.

597
00:47:58.083 --> 00:48:00.375
- Where are you taking me?
- The Royal Guard.

598
00:48:02.166 --> 00:48:03.750
{\an8}Or what's left of us. anyway.

599
00:48:04.750 --> 00:48:07.708
The Royal Guard is here?
You've been hiding?

600
00:48:08.125 --> 00:48:09.708
Skeletor would
never look for us here.

601
00:48:10.458 --> 00:48:13.750
And now that we have
the Sword. we can beat him.

602
00:48:16.625 --> 00:48:19.875
Keep it close and try not
to draw attention to yourself.

603
00:48:21.958 --> 00:48:23.583
Is that what
people wear on Earth?

604
00:48:25.958 --> 00:48:28.250
Actually. no.
Not really.

605
00:48:32.458 --> 00:48:33.458
Don't stare.

606
00:48:35.250 --> 00:48:36.583
I have eyes on the Sword.

607
00:48:47.958 --> 00:48:50.541
Okay. let me do the talking.

608
00:48:50.708 --> 00:48:52.708
These guys
might be a bit upset with...

609
00:48:54.750 --> 00:48:56.166
Where have you been?

610
00:48:56.291 --> 00:48:57.708
You were supposed
to be on patrol.

611
00:48:57.875 --> 00:48:59.458
Skeletor's goons
are everywhere.

612
00:48:59.625 --> 00:49:01.583
I found
the Sword of Power.

613
00:49:03.416 --> 00:49:04.416
What?

614
00:49:05.750 --> 00:49:09.791
There. And the man carrying it
is the son of King Randor.

615
00:49:11.500 --> 00:49:13.500
The long-lost
Prince of Eternos.

616
00:49:16.833 --> 00:49:18.083
Hi. sir.

617
00:49:18.958 --> 00:49:20.041
It's a...

618
00:49:21.250 --> 00:49:22.875
It's a real thrill to be here.

619
00:49:25.750 --> 00:49:27.125
This is no son of the king.

620
00:49:27.291 --> 00:49:30.125
He is. And he can prove it.

621
00:49:31.750 --> 00:49:33.583
I can. yes.

622
00:49:35.291 --> 00:49:36.291
So...

623
00:49:46.458 --> 00:49:48.875
I remember watching you.
as a kid with my dad.

624
00:49:49.000 --> 00:49:50.375
and seeing you
lead combat drills.

625
00:49:51.791 --> 00:49:54.125
What? Is that
an earthquake? What?

626
00:49:56.291 --> 00:49:57.500
Who is this little oik?

627
00:49:58.291 --> 00:49:59.291
Ram Man?

628
00:50:00.750 --> 00:50:01.833
What did you call me?

629
00:50:02.458 --> 00:50:03.458
Ram Man?

630
00:50:03.875 --> 00:50:05.041
You know. because...

631
00:50:05.166 --> 00:50:07.791
Well. I... I called you that
because he looks like a...

632
00:50:07.916 --> 00:50:09.208
Looks like what?

633
00:50:11.958 --> 00:50:14.583
A man who rams.

634
00:50:14.875 --> 00:50:16.708
Imposter. You don't know us.

635
00:50:17.291 --> 00:50:19.291
No. no. no.
I... I do know you.

636
00:50:19.416 --> 00:50:21.916
Well. I've been telling people

637
00:50:22.041 --> 00:50:24.208
about you guys my whole life.

638
00:50:24.375 --> 00:50:26.333
When I was a kid.
I'd make these drawings.

639
00:50:26.458 --> 00:50:27.500
so I'd never forget you.

640
00:50:28.125 --> 00:50:29.916
-Is that so?
-Yeah.

641
00:50:30.041 --> 00:50:31.958
Mm. Well. who am I then?

642
00:50:36.625 --> 00:50:38.791
You're Fisto.

643
00:50:43.833 --> 00:50:46.875
I know that's not your
proper name. but you know.

644
00:50:47.583 --> 00:50:48.708
you fist people. so...

645
00:50:48.833 --> 00:50:51.208
I don't fist people.

646
00:50:51.375 --> 00:50:53.333
I'm pretty sure I saw you
fist a goblin one time.

647
00:50:53.458 --> 00:50:54.583
Adam!

648
00:50:54.750 --> 00:50:56.583
This is the savior of Eternia?

649
00:50:56.750 --> 00:50:59.791
Look. I know. He's not
what I expected either. okay?

650
00:50:59.916 --> 00:51:02.000
But I swear it's him.

651
00:51:02.166 --> 00:51:04.208
I mean. I tracked down
the Sword of Power...

652
00:51:04.333 --> 00:51:06.625
-Let me see this.
-...and it led me to...

653
00:51:06.750 --> 00:51:08.375
- Stop squirming!
- What are you doing?

654
00:51:08.708 --> 00:51:10.375
-This guy.
-Give it.

655
00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:11.541
Teela.

656
00:51:14.958 --> 00:51:16.125
Thank you.

657
00:51:16.250 --> 00:51:18.000
I'll be honest. I thought
this would go better.

658
00:51:18.958 --> 00:51:20.916
We're going to need a minute
to talk this over.

659
00:51:21.583 --> 00:51:22.583
Sure. Yeah. yeah.

660
00:51:22.708 --> 00:51:23.708
-Let's talk it over.
-No. no. Adam!

661
00:51:23.833 --> 00:51:24.833
Uh-uh-uh.

662
00:51:28.208 --> 00:51:30.291
It's Dina. right? Dina?

663
00:51:30.458 --> 00:51:32.166
- Dian.
- Dian.

664
00:51:32.958 --> 00:51:35.416
Dian. Yes! Oh. my God.

665
00:51:35.541 --> 00:51:36.791
All right.
this is super crazy.

666
00:51:36.916 --> 00:51:39.000
but we used to go
to school together.

667
00:51:39.125 --> 00:51:41.750
You used to push me into
the lockers.

668
00:51:41.875 --> 00:51:43.583
Aw. Did it hurt?

669
00:51:44.208 --> 00:51:46.208
Well. I... Whoa!

670
00:51:51.916 --> 00:51:56.041
Dian? I think you locked it.
On accident.

671
00:51:58.333 --> 00:51:59.333
Fisto?

672
00:51:59.500 --> 00:52:01.250
It's because
he has a massive...

673
00:52:02.375 --> 00:52:03.833
I was 10. okay?

674
00:52:03.958 --> 00:52:05.166
We have
to get out of here.

675
00:52:09.541 --> 00:52:11.625
It smells
like a urinal in here.

676
00:52:13.875 --> 00:52:14.916
Oh.

677
00:52:15.833 --> 00:52:17.666
- It's him.
- Piss off.

678
00:52:17.791 --> 00:52:19.375
Yep. totally fair.

679
00:52:24.875 --> 00:52:26.416
Is that a Class-4 Battlebot?

680
00:52:26.791 --> 00:52:31.291
What? No. it's nothing.
Service bot. Glorified maid.

681
00:52:31.458 --> 00:52:32.458
Charming.

682
00:52:32.583 --> 00:52:34.333
No. Class-4s are the deadliest

683
00:52:34.458 --> 00:52:35.958
super soldiers
ever engineered.

684
00:52:36.083 --> 00:52:40.083
Just one of these bots
is worth about 15 soldiers.

685
00:52:40.375 --> 00:52:42.083
It's actually 20.

686
00:52:42.875 --> 00:52:43.875
Dope.

687
00:52:48.875 --> 00:52:50.708
It looks
like the Sword of Power.

688
00:52:53.625 --> 00:52:55.166
It's smaller than I thought.

689
00:52:55.291 --> 00:52:57.541
Well. that's just
because my hand is so big.

690
00:52:58.125 --> 00:52:59.666
Your big hand
is your other hand.

691
00:53:01.458 --> 00:53:02.916
Well. this one's
pretty big. too.

692
00:53:03.041 --> 00:53:05.000
That's why the Sword looks
so small when I hold it.

693
00:53:06.291 --> 00:53:08.291
<i>Captain.</i>

694
00:53:09.583 --> 00:53:10.583
Yeah. go ahead.

695
00:53:10.708 --> 00:53:12.541
We may have
a situation out front.

696
00:53:29.791 --> 00:53:31.250
They're coming for the Sword!

697
00:53:32.583 --> 00:53:33.875
We have to get out of here.

698
00:53:37.500 --> 00:53:41.625
Miss? You don't belong
down here mopping the floors.

699
00:53:42.375 --> 00:53:43.583
You could join us.

700
00:53:44.000 --> 00:53:45.041
As a servant?

701
00:53:45.166 --> 00:53:46.166
No. as a soldier.

702
00:53:46.291 --> 00:53:47.291
Adam. can you please

703
00:53:47.416 --> 00:53:49.083
stop making friends
with the appliances?

704
00:53:59.541 --> 00:54:00.541
I'll join you

705
00:54:00.666 --> 00:54:02.875
on the condition that
I don't make any food.

706
00:54:03.000 --> 00:54:04.000
I don't wash anything.

707
00:54:04.125 --> 00:54:05.291
and any fluids of any type

708
00:54:05.416 --> 00:54:07.458
that come out of you
are yours to deal with.

709
00:54:07.583 --> 00:54:08.708
Got it?

710
00:54:12.125 --> 00:54:13.125
Wait.

711
00:54:14.208 --> 00:54:15.208
Hold on.

712
00:54:15.875 --> 00:54:17.583
Help me get him up.
I can't leave him.

713
00:54:17.750 --> 00:54:19.541
- What? The drunk guy?
- Dad.

714
00:54:19.666 --> 00:54:20.750
Wake up.

715
00:54:20.875 --> 00:54:21.875
Why...

716
00:54:22.541 --> 00:54:23.916
Why'd you call him Dad?

717
00:54:24.083 --> 00:54:25.250
He's my dad.

718
00:54:25.750 --> 00:54:27.416
Dad. wake up.

719
00:54:27.541 --> 00:54:30.375
Keep it down.
I'm trying to sleep here.

720
00:54:30.500 --> 00:54:31.500
Duncan?

721
00:54:31.625 --> 00:54:32.708
Are you going to help me
get him up or not?

722
00:54:32.833 --> 00:54:34.750
Yeah.

723
00:54:35.958 --> 00:54:37.583
Okay.

724
00:54:37.708 --> 00:54:38.916
Oh. my God. he's heavy.

725
00:54:43.000 --> 00:54:44.291
Yeah. good idea.
He needs to hydrate.

726
00:54:50.208 --> 00:54:53.083
Who's this guy? Do I know you?

727
00:54:54.083 --> 00:54:55.500
Well. yeah. Yeah.

728
00:54:57.291 --> 00:54:58.291
Um...

729
00:54:59.666 --> 00:55:03.250
A long time ago. when I was
a kid. you used to train me.

730
00:55:05.166 --> 00:55:08.250
Sword fighting?
Hand-to-hand combat?

731
00:55:09.875 --> 00:55:12.916
Oh. you... you berated me.
kicked me while I was down.

732
00:55:13.083 --> 00:55:15.750
demoralized me. totally
destroyed my self-esteem?

733
00:55:17.708 --> 00:55:19.166
Mm.

734
00:55:19.625 --> 00:55:20.625
Uh...

735
00:55:21.375 --> 00:55:22.458
Adam. I'm...

736
00:55:23.583 --> 00:55:25.291
Adam.

737
00:55:25.750 --> 00:55:26.958
Ugh!

738
00:55:27.083 --> 00:55:28.083
I'm not
cleaning that up.

739
00:55:28.208 --> 00:55:29.583
Nobody asked you
to clean it up.

740
00:55:32.166 --> 00:55:33.625
Wait a minute.
I know who you are.

741
00:55:34.583 --> 00:55:35.916
You're Randor's son.

742
00:55:36.083 --> 00:55:38.500
Yeah. Yeah. it's me.

743
00:55:38.625 --> 00:55:40.083
Sweet little Adam.

744
00:55:40.208 --> 00:55:43.208
Adam! Oh. this is so cool!
You remember me.

745
00:55:43.333 --> 00:55:45.416
Weedy. Namby-pamby.

746
00:55:45.541 --> 00:55:47.291
- Like weak.
- Whoa.

747
00:55:47.416 --> 00:55:49.750
Okay. I don't think I was...
Namby-pamby?

748
00:55:49.875 --> 00:55:51.625
All right. that's it.

749
00:55:51.750 --> 00:55:52.916
We're leaving.
Come on. We got to go. Dad.

750
00:55:53.041 --> 00:55:54.166
- What? No. no. no.
- Let's go.

751
00:55:54.333 --> 00:55:56.083
I'm perfectly fine right here.
You guys leave.

752
00:55:56.208 --> 00:55:58.041
I'm staying here
next to this vomit.

753
00:56:02.875 --> 00:56:04.291
We're going
to have to carry him.

754
00:56:05.041 --> 00:56:06.041
Mm-hmm.

755
00:56:11.791 --> 00:56:13.125
Oh. I see.

756
00:56:13.250 --> 00:56:16.791
Thank you so much for inviting
me on this exciting adventure.

757
00:56:20.000 --> 00:56:21.750
Hey.

758
00:56:21.875 --> 00:56:25.041
Hey. I can walk.
I said I can walk!

759
00:56:28.291 --> 00:56:29.875
- This way.
- Oh. Oh!

760
00:56:37.958 --> 00:56:40.916
The Sword is here. Find it!

761
00:56:41.666 --> 00:56:42.666
You've got to get the Sword

762
00:56:42.791 --> 00:56:45.125
as far away from him
as possible. Go!

763
00:56:49.083 --> 00:56:50.250
Come on. we got to go.

764
00:56:51.708 --> 00:56:53.000
What's going on here?

765
00:57:02.833 --> 00:57:05.125
Hey. asshole robot!

766
00:57:05.291 --> 00:57:07.541
I told you I could walk.

767
00:57:07.666 --> 00:57:08.791
Uh.
you might want to duck.

768
00:57:08.916 --> 00:57:10.791
You might want to get fu...

769
00:57:15.416 --> 00:57:17.541
Roboto. could you please
deploy battle mode

770
00:57:17.666 --> 00:57:19.041
for. like. one second?

771
00:57:19.166 --> 00:57:20.583
Are you
trying to be funny?

772
00:57:20.750 --> 00:57:21.833
She's a service bot.

773
00:57:21.958 --> 00:57:23.291
Duncan reprogrammed her
years ago.

774
00:57:23.416 --> 00:57:24.750
You're damn right I did.

775
00:57:24.875 --> 00:57:26.250
Maniac nearly
shot my head off.

776
00:57:26.416 --> 00:57:27.666
It was a malfunction.

777
00:57:27.791 --> 00:57:28.791
Yeah. right.

778
00:57:33.750 --> 00:57:34.750
Run.

779
00:57:35.041 --> 00:57:36.791
What the hell
is happening?

780
00:57:37.500 --> 00:57:38.958
Stop shooting at me!

781
00:57:41.166 --> 00:57:42.166
Thanks. guys.

782
00:57:44.291 --> 00:57:45.333
Follow me.

783
00:57:46.791 --> 00:57:48.291
Whoa! Did she jump?

784
00:57:48.583 --> 00:57:49.791
I was
not expecting that.

785
00:57:50.083 --> 00:57:51.500
Yeah. No. me neither.

786
00:57:53.458 --> 00:57:54.500
You want me
to carry Drunkan?

787
00:57:54.625 --> 00:57:55.875
-What'd you call me?
-Okay.

788
00:57:56.000 --> 00:57:57.625
Duncan. you good?

789
00:58:00.708 --> 00:58:01.791
Never better.

790
00:58:01.916 --> 00:58:03.750
Oh!

791
00:58:03.875 --> 00:58:05.500
Ow!

792
00:58:11.041 --> 00:58:12.708
How is he
not dead yet?

793
00:58:12.958 --> 00:58:14.666
- No. I'm good.
- Dad.

794
00:58:15.416 --> 00:58:16.416
Let's go.

795
00:58:18.208 --> 00:58:19.916
Okay. All right.

796
00:58:22.166 --> 00:58:23.916
Come out. cowards!

797
00:58:24.708 --> 00:58:25.708
Trap Jaw.

798
00:58:25.875 --> 00:58:26.875
Who?

799
00:58:27.416 --> 00:58:28.500
- It's from my drawings!
- Trap Jaw?

800
00:58:28.625 --> 00:58:31.583
-Never mind.
-No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

801
00:58:31.708 --> 00:58:32.708
Dad.

802
00:58:32.833 --> 00:58:35.083
Anyone but him. We're trapped.

803
00:58:35.541 --> 00:58:37.833
There's nowhere left to run.

804
00:58:37.958 --> 00:58:41.166
Maybe... Maybe I could
talk to him. Start a dialogue.

805
00:58:41.333 --> 00:58:42.375
-Are you out of your mind?
-What?

806
00:58:42.500 --> 00:58:43.833
-Is he out of his mind?
-A dialogue?

807
00:58:43.958 --> 00:58:45.958
I do this for work
all the time.

808
00:58:46.125 --> 00:58:47.958
I'm actually
kind of good at it.

809
00:58:48.125 --> 00:58:49.416
-Hey. no.
-I'll be right back.

810
00:58:49.541 --> 00:58:50.541
-No!
-I'll be right back.

811
00:58:50.666 --> 00:58:51.666
- What?
- Adam!

812
00:58:55.625 --> 00:58:56.708
Hello!

813
00:58:58.333 --> 00:58:59.416
Hello.

814
00:59:00.875 --> 00:59:02.291
Mr. Trap Jaw.

815
00:59:02.666 --> 00:59:03.666
Hi there. uh...

816
00:59:04.416 --> 00:59:05.458
Wait.

817
00:59:06.750 --> 00:59:08.541
Could I talk to you
for a second?

818
00:59:08.666 --> 00:59:11.791
I just want to de-escalate
the situation here

819
00:59:11.916 --> 00:59:15.875
because it feels like emotions
are running super high.

820
00:59:16.041 --> 00:59:19.750
Oh. they are. are they?

821
00:59:19.875 --> 00:59:21.125
And who might you be?

822
00:59:21.250 --> 00:59:23.208
I'm Adam. Prince of...

823
00:59:27.000 --> 00:59:28.041
Okay.

824
00:59:28.166 --> 00:59:32.083
I can see that we're heading
into conflict territory here.

825
00:59:34.416 --> 00:59:36.416
Stop talking.

826
00:59:36.833 --> 00:59:38.791
Okay.

827
00:59:38.958 --> 00:59:40.458
And conflict resolution

828
00:59:40.583 --> 00:59:44.041
relies on effective
communication. right?

829
00:59:53.875 --> 00:59:55.208
Whoa!

830
01:00:21.666 --> 01:00:23.125
Use the Sword!

831
01:00:23.291 --> 01:00:24.708
Use the sword. What sword?

832
01:00:39.958 --> 01:00:41.583
Say the words.

833
01:00:42.708 --> 01:00:43.750
Whoa.

834
01:00:53.666 --> 01:00:54.916
By the Power...

835
01:01:00.041 --> 01:01:01.833
By the Power of Grayskull.

836
01:01:02.750 --> 01:01:05.583
By the Power of Grayskull!

837
01:01:54.666 --> 01:01:58.083
I have the Power!

838
01:02:13.291 --> 01:02:15.583
Oh. wow.

839
01:02:17.125 --> 01:02:18.416
Wow.

840
01:02:18.541 --> 01:02:20.333
The champion of Grayskull!

841
01:02:22.500 --> 01:02:23.666
We're saved.

842
01:02:29.875 --> 01:02:31.625
We're screwed.

843
01:03:16.833 --> 01:03:17.833
Holy...

844
01:03:37.250 --> 01:03:38.875
That's it.
That's what I taught you.

845
01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:41.291
-That's not... Okay.
-That's good. It's good.

846
01:03:53.708 --> 01:03:54.750
Ooh!

847
01:04:01.083 --> 01:04:03.833
-Hey. we got to move. Come on.
-Let's go.

848
01:04:13.166 --> 01:04:14.458
You guys see that?

849
01:04:14.875 --> 01:04:17.541
I ripped that dude's arm off
and I shot all his friends.

850
01:04:17.666 --> 01:04:19.291
I saw that. lad. I saw it.

851
01:04:42.333 --> 01:04:43.916
Mm...

852
01:04:47.208 --> 01:04:51.875
You fools!
You dolts and blockheads!

853
01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:53.041
My lord!

854
01:04:53.208 --> 01:04:56.500
Oh. you pathetic pail
of pitiful pissants!

855
01:04:56.625 --> 01:04:57.916
I want that sword!
Do you hear me?

856
01:04:58.041 --> 01:05:00.000
I want that sword. It's mine.

857
01:05:00.125 --> 01:05:02.750
Mine. mine. mine. mine.
Mine. mine. mine.

858
01:05:02.875 --> 01:05:05.250
And I will have it.
Do you hear me?

859
01:05:05.375 --> 01:05:10.291
I will have it. And you.
you... you will get it for me.

860
01:05:13.166 --> 01:05:14.166
Whew.

861
01:05:15.250 --> 01:05:17.250
Do you understand?

862
01:05:17.791 --> 01:05:19.666
After them! Get the Sword!

863
01:05:48.583 --> 01:05:49.708
Maybe I should fly.

864
01:05:49.875 --> 01:05:50.958
You're not flying. Dad.

865
01:05:56.958 --> 01:05:57.958
You're doing great. Teela.

866
01:05:58.125 --> 01:05:59.875
-Not now. Adam.
-Okay.

867
01:06:17.500 --> 01:06:18.958
- Ugh! Son of a...
<i>- Breach.</i>

868
01:06:19.083 --> 01:06:20.125
{\an8}<i>Hull breach.</i>

869
01:06:20.250 --> 01:06:21.833
Ship. run analytics.

870
01:06:21.958 --> 01:06:24.708
<i>Running analytics.</i>
<i>My hull is breached.</i>

871
01:06:24.833 --> 01:06:25.833
Got it.

872
01:06:25.958 --> 01:06:27.625
I'm just saying. I have a lot
of experience when it comes

873
01:06:27.750 --> 01:06:28.958
-to. like. you know...
-Do you want to walk. Dad?

874
01:06:29.083 --> 01:06:30.083
Because I'll make you walk.

875
01:06:34.041 --> 01:06:35.125
Oh. shit.

876
01:06:40.083 --> 01:06:41.166
Teela?

877
01:06:41.291 --> 01:06:42.416
Go out there
and shoot some bad guys.

878
01:06:42.833 --> 01:06:44.208
-Okay.
-Sky sled. In the back.

879
01:06:44.375 --> 01:06:45.791
I'm on it. Sky sled.

880
01:06:45.916 --> 01:06:47.416
-Not you.
-What?

881
01:06:47.541 --> 01:06:48.625
Definitely not you.

882
01:06:48.750 --> 01:06:50.416
Okay.

883
01:07:11.708 --> 01:07:13.041
Whoa!

884
01:07:13.166 --> 01:07:14.583
What the...?

885
01:07:14.708 --> 01:07:16.000
Okay.

886
01:07:18.083 --> 01:07:19.083
Yeah.

887
01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:29.083
Whoa!

888
01:07:53.375 --> 01:07:54.375
Whoa!

889
01:08:01.541 --> 01:08:02.625
We're losing altitude.

890
01:08:02.750 --> 01:08:03.916
You know.
if you put less pressure

891
01:08:04.041 --> 01:08:05.833
-on the yoke. you'll get...
-Not one word.

892
01:09:05.416 --> 01:09:06.416
We're not going to make it.

893
01:09:06.541 --> 01:09:08.791
Teela. hold her
as steady as you can.

894
01:09:08.916 --> 01:09:10.291
Oh. says the drunk guy.

895
01:09:12.958 --> 01:09:14.000
Whoa!

896
01:09:14.125 --> 01:09:15.708
Whoa.

897
01:09:24.916 --> 01:09:25.916
All right.

898
01:09:33.916 --> 01:09:34.916
Adam?

899
01:09:38.500 --> 01:09:40.208
Adam! Hey!

900
01:09:40.333 --> 01:09:43.125
Hey. look out behind you!

901
01:09:47.708 --> 01:09:50.000
-Get out of there. you moron.
-What?

902
01:09:53.208 --> 01:09:54.208
You're going to die.

903
01:11:01.916 --> 01:11:04.250
Wow. you can really fly.

904
01:11:06.125 --> 01:11:07.666
I don't want to hear it.

905
01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:11.208
Insurgents
of Eternia.

906
01:11:11.791 --> 01:11:14.666
Your long reprieve
has come to an end.

907
01:11:14.791 --> 01:11:17.208
You are done.

908
01:11:19.416 --> 01:11:21.791
Well. if you would live
to see another morning.

909
01:11:22.291 --> 01:11:25.333
I now demand your fealty.

910
01:11:26.041 --> 01:11:28.541
Do you know
what that means. miscreant?

911
01:11:29.625 --> 01:11:34.083
It means I shall kill you
one by one

912
01:11:34.208 --> 01:11:38.333
until you tell me the name
of that insolent barbarian.

913
01:11:39.666 --> 01:11:42.166
And do you know who I mean?

914
01:11:43.208 --> 01:11:46.458
Muscles. Loincloth.
All over tan.

915
01:11:46.583 --> 01:11:49.125
Big. shiny sword.

916
01:11:49.250 --> 01:11:50.333
Mm.

917
01:11:54.500 --> 01:11:55.500
No?

918
01:11:57.916 --> 01:11:59.916
Very well.

919
01:12:04.958 --> 01:12:06.125
You.

920
01:12:06.875 --> 01:12:08.916
- Evil-Lyn. who is this?
- Um...

921
01:12:09.916 --> 01:12:11.750
Moss Man.

922
01:12:12.250 --> 01:12:13.583
He'll do. Mm.

923
01:12:13.708 --> 01:12:15.791
No! No. no.

924
01:12:17.750 --> 01:12:20.791
Watch.
fallen heroes of Eternia.

925
01:12:21.291 --> 01:12:24.833
as he begs
for his miserable life.

926
01:12:26.208 --> 01:12:27.208
Go on.

927
01:12:28.458 --> 01:12:29.916
Beg.

928
01:12:30.083 --> 01:12:31.375
No.

929
01:12:31.500 --> 01:12:33.291
No!

930
01:12:36.875 --> 01:12:39.708
Oh. look.
darling. I made mulch.

931
01:12:43.041 --> 01:12:45.083
Very good. Mulch.

932
01:12:56.041 --> 01:12:57.791
So I ask again.

933
01:12:57.916 --> 01:13:02.208
who is the warrior
who fought for you today?

934
01:13:02.750 --> 01:13:03.916
No more!

935
01:13:04.041 --> 01:13:05.333
No more. I'll tell.

936
01:13:05.458 --> 01:13:06.916
Oh. please do.

937
01:13:07.041 --> 01:13:09.500
It's the young prince.
returned from the dead.

938
01:13:13.000 --> 01:13:14.500
Is it indeed?

939
01:13:15.125 --> 01:13:17.625
Take them all away.
Lock them up.

940
01:13:17.750 --> 01:13:20.416
Let this midden burn
to the ground.

941
01:13:25.250 --> 01:13:27.166
Well. they're not going
to follow us in here.

942
01:13:28.875 --> 01:13:31.125
Not without reinforcements.

943
01:13:31.291 --> 01:13:32.833
I'm going to go look for Adam
while there's still light.

944
01:13:32.958 --> 01:13:34.791
No. no. no. no.
you leave that to me.

945
01:13:34.958 --> 01:13:37.000
-Really. Dad. I got it.
-Teela. This is what I do.

946
01:13:38.125 --> 01:13:40.458
Did. This is what you did.

947
01:13:40.583 --> 01:13:43.250
I am handling this. Stay here.

948
01:14:36.625 --> 01:14:38.125
Where am I?

949
01:14:45.250 --> 01:14:46.291
Who am I?

950
01:14:46.416 --> 01:14:47.500
<i>You are he</i>

951
01:14:47.625 --> 01:14:50.125
<i>who will restore peace</i>
<i>to Eternia.</i>

952
01:14:51.458 --> 01:14:54.208
<i>The Champion of Grayskull.</i>

953
01:15:12.875 --> 01:15:14.250
Adam.

954
01:15:17.000 --> 01:15:19.083
Thank Zodac.
you're alive!

955
01:15:19.208 --> 01:15:21.125
I think you just
shooed off the Sorceress.

956
01:15:22.958 --> 01:15:24.958
That's not the Sorceress.

957
01:15:25.375 --> 01:15:27.458
I really think that
that was the Sorceress.

958
01:15:28.583 --> 01:15:29.583
Sure.

959
01:15:30.541 --> 01:15:31.541
Are you hurt?

960
01:15:32.125 --> 01:15:33.583
Weirdly. not at all.

961
01:15:35.375 --> 01:15:36.375
Good.

962
01:15:42.291 --> 01:15:44.750
Come on. it's getting dark.

963
01:15:48.958 --> 01:15:50.333
We'll camp here tonight.

964
01:15:50.458 --> 01:15:51.875
get moving
first thing tomorrow.

965
01:15:59.333 --> 01:16:00.333
What?

966
01:16:00.833 --> 01:16:04.250
Nothing. Just haven't seen you
like this in a while.

967
01:16:04.416 --> 01:16:08.500
Well. Man-At-Arms
is in here somewhere.

968
01:16:09.083 --> 01:16:10.416
I hope you find him.

969
01:16:11.416 --> 01:16:13.416
Hey. wait a second.

970
01:16:15.458 --> 01:16:16.791
What have we got here?

971
01:16:18.958 --> 01:16:20.833
Oh. who's up for a drink?

972
01:16:21.083 --> 01:16:23.458
Dad. are you serious?

973
01:16:23.625 --> 01:16:26.166
What? Come on. Sit down.

974
01:16:26.333 --> 01:16:27.333
Let's crack open a few.

975
01:16:27.458 --> 01:16:29.000
Tell some stories.
sing some songs.

976
01:16:29.166 --> 01:16:31.000
If we don't celebrate
the small victories...

977
01:16:31.166 --> 01:16:33.541
Victory? What victory?

978
01:16:33.708 --> 01:16:34.958
Well. we didn't die.

979
01:16:35.125 --> 01:16:36.541
Oh. that's a victory for you?

980
01:16:36.708 --> 01:16:38.458
Teela. I say we earned it.

981
01:16:38.625 --> 01:16:41.083
You've been "earning it"
for 15 years.

982
01:16:49.666 --> 01:16:52.625
More for you and me.
Come on. Sit down.

983
01:16:57.875 --> 01:16:59.916
Here's to the return
of the Sword

984
01:17:00.083 --> 01:17:04.000
and the Champion of Grayskull!

985
01:17:04.333 --> 01:17:05.541
Ripping some dude's arm off

986
01:17:05.708 --> 01:17:06.958
doesn't really seem like
the kind of thing

987
01:17:07.083 --> 01:17:08.291
that we should be celebrating.

988
01:17:08.791 --> 01:17:10.291
Well. it was you or him.

989
01:17:10.750 --> 01:17:12.583
Like. whatever happened to...

990
01:17:12.708 --> 01:17:16.375
to understanding
and listening?

991
01:17:17.416 --> 01:17:18.541
Just talking to one another?

992
01:17:18.708 --> 01:17:19.958
Oh. talk.

993
01:17:20.125 --> 01:17:21.916
What are you going to do
when a guy charges

994
01:17:22.041 --> 01:17:23.666
towards your family
with a sword?

995
01:17:23.833 --> 01:17:25.416
Okay. I get it.
What I'm supposed to say...?

996
01:17:25.541 --> 01:17:26.541
You... You fight him. right?

997
01:17:26.666 --> 01:17:29.208
No. you protect them.

998
01:17:29.375 --> 01:17:31.708
You... You're thinking
about it all wrong.

999
01:17:31.875 --> 01:17:33.583
I mean. you scoff
at the trigger-happy grunts!

1000
01:17:33.708 --> 01:17:35.041
Look how backward
they all are.

1001
01:17:35.166 --> 01:17:36.458
But when the war breaks out.

1002
01:17:36.583 --> 01:17:38.166
it's not the poets
that step up.

1003
01:17:38.333 --> 01:17:39.875
It's the man with the muscle.

1004
01:17:40.041 --> 01:17:41.958
And he's not doing it
for glory.

1005
01:17:45.583 --> 01:17:47.041
He's doing it so his...

1006
01:17:48.375 --> 01:17:50.708
his children can see
another morning.

1007
01:17:50.875 --> 01:17:53.708
That is a man.
as far as I can tell.

1008
01:17:54.416 --> 01:17:57.041
He stands up
when he is needed.

1009
01:17:58.958 --> 01:18:00.041
Like you did.

1010
01:18:01.708 --> 01:18:02.833
Speaking of which.

1011
01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:06.875
you. uh...
you weren't bad earlier on.

1012
01:18:10.291 --> 01:18:13.208
That's the nicest thing
you've ever said to me.

1013
01:18:13.375 --> 01:18:15.458
I mean. your form.
it's a little shoddy.

1014
01:18:15.625 --> 01:18:17.875
And your technique
could do some work.

1015
01:18:18.041 --> 01:18:19.958
-But. uh. not bad.
-There he is.

1016
01:18:20.125 --> 01:18:22.000
There's the Duncan I remember.

1017
01:18:23.041 --> 01:18:25.166
Um. good.

1018
01:18:43.833 --> 01:18:46.875
Hey. can you come
help me with this?

1019
01:18:56.291 --> 01:18:57.375
Whoa.

1020
01:18:58.958 --> 01:18:59.958
It is quite heavy.

1021
01:19:00.083 --> 01:19:01.291
-so if you could just...
-Oh. my God! Yeah.

1022
01:19:01.875 --> 01:19:03.416
Yeah.

1023
01:19:03.541 --> 01:19:05.000
Your. um...

1024
01:19:05.125 --> 01:19:06.458
Your loincloth is in my...

1025
01:19:06.583 --> 01:19:07.875
-Sorry.
-Fine.

1026
01:19:19.375 --> 01:19:24.291
So. how does it feel
to be the mighty warrior?

1027
01:19:25.541 --> 01:19:26.791
Uh...

1028
01:19:29.125 --> 01:19:34.416
All things considered. I feel
pretty great.

1029
01:19:34.541 --> 01:19:36.500
I'm not quite sure what
happened to my shirt though.

1030
01:19:36.625 --> 01:19:38.916
Or my pants.

1031
01:19:39.416 --> 01:19:41.375
Do those come back.

1032
01:19:41.500 --> 01:19:43.625
or do I have to buy
a new pair every time?

1033
01:19:44.416 --> 01:19:46.041
I really missed you. you know.

1034
01:19:47.875 --> 01:19:48.875
Me too.

1035
01:19:51.750 --> 01:19:55.083
I thought about you.
All the time.

1036
01:19:59.375 --> 01:20:00.375
Me too.

1037
01:20:02.458 --> 01:20:04.333
Honestly.
there wasn't a day went by

1038
01:20:04.458 --> 01:20:05.708
I didn't think about you.

1039
01:20:07.208 --> 01:20:08.208
Me too.

1040
01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:11.500
And how much...

1041
01:20:13.291 --> 01:20:15.083
our friendship means to me.

1042
01:20:16.625 --> 01:20:17.708
Hmm?

1043
01:20:17.833 --> 01:20:19.375
You were always
such a good friend.

1044
01:20:19.541 --> 01:20:21.166
Like a really.
really good friend. You know.

1045
01:20:21.291 --> 01:20:22.958
-practically a little brother.
-Hmm.

1046
01:20:23.083 --> 01:20:24.625
Yeah. You've always
been my friend

1047
01:20:24.750 --> 01:20:26.333
and you'll always
be my friend.

1048
01:20:26.500 --> 01:20:27.958
And nothing will change that.
Not ever.

1049
01:20:28.083 --> 01:20:30.833
My dawg. Whew!

1050
01:20:30.958 --> 01:20:31.958
-Phew. I know. Okay.
-Yeah.

1051
01:20:32.083 --> 01:20:33.125
-All right.
-Weight off of me.

1052
01:20:33.250 --> 01:20:34.458
Well. let's go
confiscate that flask

1053
01:20:34.583 --> 01:20:35.750
before my dad starts singing.

1054
01:20:36.291 --> 01:20:38.125
Yeah. we don't...
we don't want that.

1055
01:20:38.291 --> 01:20:39.625
- Yeah.
- We...

1056
01:20:50.500 --> 01:20:54.083
Behold insignificant wretches.
it is I.

1057
01:20:54.750 --> 01:20:56.208
Skeletor.

1058
01:20:56.750 --> 01:21:01.500
And you are but worms
beneath my feet.

1059
01:21:01.666 --> 01:21:04.916
Butt-worms?
He just called us butt-worms.

1060
01:21:05.375 --> 01:21:06.750
Yet there is one
among you

1061
01:21:06.875 --> 01:21:08.708
who thinks
he has a higher purpose.

1062
01:21:08.875 --> 01:21:12.833
It seems the prodigal prince
has returned.

1063
01:21:13.000 --> 01:21:16.750
But this is not your Eternia
anymore. Prince Adam.

1064
01:21:17.583 --> 01:21:21.125
It is mine.
And so is everything in it.

1065
01:21:21.791 --> 01:21:24.250
Including that sword
you carry.

1066
01:21:24.416 --> 01:21:28.250
for it is fit for a far
mightier hand than yours.

1067
01:21:29.583 --> 01:21:33.541
So. here
is my magnanimous offer.

1068
01:21:33.708 --> 01:21:36.333
Bring the Sword of Power to me
at Snake Mountain

1069
01:21:36.500 --> 01:21:39.875
and you might yet
be reconciled with your...

1070
01:21:40.041 --> 01:21:42.708
mummy and daddy.

1071
01:21:42.833 --> 01:21:46.750
Yes. they're alive and well.

1072
01:21:47.625 --> 01:21:51.416
Okay. not "well."
but they're alive.

1073
01:21:53.041 --> 01:21:57.416
Imagine. you could be
a happy family together again.

1074
01:21:59.000 --> 01:22:01.833
Or they could die...

1075
01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:03.000
horribly.

1076
01:22:04.333 --> 01:22:07.666
And that will forever
be on you.

1077
01:22:08.625 --> 01:22:12.375
Oh. how heavy will that sword
weigh in your hand then.

1078
01:22:13.041 --> 01:22:14.958
Champion of Grayskull?

1079
01:22:26.333 --> 01:22:27.625
I have to leave.

1080
01:22:28.500 --> 01:22:29.500
Now.

1081
01:22:29.875 --> 01:22:32.416
Adam! Adam! It's a trap!

1082
01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:34.625
We can't let Skeletor
get his hands on the Sword.

1083
01:22:34.750 --> 01:22:35.750
He'd be unstoppable.

1084
01:22:35.875 --> 01:22:37.666
I'm not going
to give him the Sword.

1085
01:22:37.791 --> 01:22:39.000
I'm going to kill him with it.

1086
01:22:39.291 --> 01:22:40.625
This is Skeletor
we're talking about.

1087
01:22:40.750 --> 01:22:41.875
You can't just charge
into this.

1088
01:22:42.208 --> 01:22:45.708
I have the
power of a god in my hands.

1089
01:22:45.875 --> 01:22:49.333
But you are not a god.
You're a man.

1090
01:22:49.500 --> 01:22:51.250
He took my family. Teela!

1091
01:22:53.041 --> 01:22:54.208
I have to save them.

1092
01:22:56.958 --> 01:22:59.458
It's what a man does. right?

1093
01:23:00.041 --> 01:23:03.125
You sound like my dad.

1094
01:23:03.791 --> 01:23:04.916
Is that a bad thing?

1095
01:23:05.083 --> 01:23:06.791
- We'll see.
- Hey!

1096
01:23:07.375 --> 01:23:09.208
I'm going with you
or without you.

1097
01:23:10.541 --> 01:23:11.541
Adam.

1098
01:23:14.041 --> 01:23:15.083
We're with you.

1099
01:23:19.958 --> 01:23:21.208
Every step of the way.

1100
01:23:23.083 --> 01:23:25.250
It's like
they want to die all the time.

1101
01:23:25.416 --> 01:23:26.416
Not now.

1102
01:23:32.166 --> 01:23:33.166
Come on.

1103
01:23:34.125 --> 01:23:35.833
Snake Mountain is this way.

1104
01:24:14.416 --> 01:24:16.000
We don't know
what's in there.

1105
01:24:17.166 --> 01:24:18.250
I'm in there.

1106
01:24:23.000 --> 01:24:24.250
Follow my lead.

1107
01:24:27.541 --> 01:24:28.875
Ho the...

1108
01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:30.291
Uh...

1109
01:24:30.416 --> 01:24:33.291
Hi. I am Adam.

1110
01:24:34.208 --> 01:24:35.750
Prince of Eternia

1111
01:24:35.875 --> 01:24:38.458
and defender of the secrets
of Castle Grayskull.

1112
01:24:39.250 --> 01:24:41.375
And I carry with me
the Sword of Power.

1113
01:24:46.750 --> 01:24:49.291
Surrender your weapon to me.

1114
01:24:49.458 --> 01:24:53.958
I will give the Sword
to Skeletor and Skeletor only.

1115
01:24:54.083 --> 01:24:56.208
Hmm.

1116
01:24:56.916 --> 01:24:58.291
Keep the Sword.

1117
01:24:58.583 --> 01:24:59.583
Guards!

1118
01:25:00.291 --> 01:25:01.375
Ah.

1119
01:25:10.416 --> 01:25:16.208
Take this one and his gorgeous
muscles to Lord Skeletor.

1120
01:25:17.250 --> 01:25:19.000
The rest will come with me.

1121
01:25:19.500 --> 01:25:21.166
Prepare the dungeons.

1122
01:25:22.916 --> 01:25:24.500
Adam. you give him hell!

1123
01:26:11.333 --> 01:26:14.166
Killer view.
isn't it?

1124
01:26:21.541 --> 01:26:23.541
Shall I give you two a moment?

1125
01:26:24.916 --> 01:26:25.916
Dad?

1126
01:26:26.833 --> 01:26:28.125
Adam?

1127
01:26:29.041 --> 01:26:30.541
Is it you?

1128
01:26:30.791 --> 01:26:31.875
Yeah.

1129
01:26:33.458 --> 01:26:34.541
It's me.

1130
01:26:34.916 --> 01:26:37.583
Teary
reconciliations can wait.

1131
01:26:38.125 --> 01:26:40.416
Now give me the Sword.

1132
01:26:42.750 --> 01:26:43.875
Release him.

1133
01:26:44.000 --> 01:26:47.291
Mm-hmm... I said it first.

1134
01:26:47.458 --> 01:26:48.458
Release him!

1135
01:26:49.208 --> 01:26:52.583
You don't want to play that
game with me. you naughty boy.

1136
01:26:52.750 --> 01:26:54.666
I play to win and...

1137
01:26:56.041 --> 01:26:57.541
I cheat.

1138
01:27:13.125 --> 01:27:14.125
Take it.

1139
01:27:16.000 --> 01:27:17.166
You can try.

1140
01:27:55.208 --> 01:27:56.750
No. No!

1141
01:30:49.583 --> 01:30:52.458
Very good. Evil-Lyn.
he's... he's frozen.

1142
01:30:53.875 --> 01:30:56.541
Bravo. Prince Adam.
Quite the show.

1143
01:30:56.916 --> 01:30:58.583
But to what end?

1144
01:30:59.333 --> 01:31:02.000
Face me like a man.

1145
01:31:03.041 --> 01:31:04.958
Well. A.
I don't have a face.

1146
01:31:05.083 --> 01:31:07.000
and. B. I don't want to.

1147
01:31:08.125 --> 01:31:11.500
Besides. it's my turn
to put on a show.

1148
01:31:12.291 --> 01:31:14.166
What do you think. Papa?

1149
01:31:14.583 --> 01:31:15.916
Shall I let him watch

1150
01:31:16.041 --> 01:31:18.333
as I slay you
with his own sword?

1151
01:31:20.041 --> 01:31:21.041
Oh. yes.

1152
01:31:39.958 --> 01:31:40.958
No.

1153
01:31:41.750 --> 01:31:43.750
No!

1154
01:31:57.458 --> 01:31:58.875
Dad?

1155
01:32:00.333 --> 01:32:01.333
Adam.

1156
01:32:03.041 --> 01:32:04.416
Let me see you.

1157
01:32:07.791 --> 01:32:09.083
There you are.

1158
01:32:10.250 --> 01:32:14.041
Oh. you took your time.
but you came back.

1159
01:32:14.833 --> 01:32:18.250
Yeah. I've changed so much.

1160
01:32:19.583 --> 01:32:24.208
I'm not that. uh... I'm not
that weak little boy anymore.

1161
01:32:24.333 --> 01:32:26.375
Yeah.

1162
01:32:27.333 --> 01:32:29.250
Now I'm everything
you wanted me to be.

1163
01:32:30.166 --> 01:32:31.166
Well. what...

1164
01:32:32.541 --> 01:32:34.500
Well. what did I want
you to be?

1165
01:32:37.833 --> 01:32:39.166
Someone else.

1166
01:32:43.458 --> 01:32:47.875
No. No. Hey. Hey. that's...

1167
01:32:48.583 --> 01:32:50.833
That's not what I wanted.

1168
01:32:53.666 --> 01:32:58.208
As a boy.
you were so very small.

1169
01:32:59.666 --> 01:33:01.416
The world just...

1170
01:33:02.875 --> 01:33:05.208
just seemed so big for you.

1171
01:33:05.958 --> 01:33:08.375
So I tried to make you strong

1172
01:33:09.166 --> 01:33:12.333
because I wanted...
I wanted to protect you.

1173
01:33:13.791 --> 01:33:16.000
It was the only way
I knew how.

1174
01:33:17.375 --> 01:33:18.416
There are...

1175
01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:24.666
Oh. there were so many things
I should have said.

1176
01:33:25.166 --> 01:33:28.333
Dad. it's okay.

1177
01:33:28.458 --> 01:33:30.583
- Hmm?
- It's... It's okay.

1178
01:33:30.708 --> 01:33:32.958
I wish
I understood better then.

1179
01:33:34.458 --> 01:33:36.458
I wish I had let you...

1180
01:33:39.458 --> 01:33:40.625
be you.

1181
01:33:47.416 --> 01:33:50.375
Dad. no. Wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait! Wait!

1182
01:33:51.500 --> 01:33:54.833
Dad. you... you can't close
your eyes yet.

1183
01:33:56.208 --> 01:33:57.625
I didn't...

1184
01:33:57.750 --> 01:33:59.250
I didn't get
to say it yet. I...

1185
01:34:01.458 --> 01:34:07.125
I... I need you to hear...
hear me say it.

1186
01:34:18.958 --> 01:34:20.875
And so
you both submit.

1187
01:34:42.458 --> 01:34:43.666
Are you okay. lad?

1188
01:34:44.375 --> 01:34:45.500
You changed back.

1189
01:35:01.833 --> 01:35:03.750
- Mom.
- Oh.

1190
01:35:07.708 --> 01:35:08.708
Mm.

1191
01:35:11.125 --> 01:35:12.125
He's gone.

1192
01:35:19.958 --> 01:35:20.958
Oh.

1193
01:35:22.500 --> 01:35:24.583
<i>Oh.</i>
<i>so long I've waited.</i>

1194
01:35:27.333 --> 01:35:29.708
Now I shall be reborn

1195
01:35:30.750 --> 01:35:34.500
and the universe
shall quake in my shadow.

1196
01:35:36.666 --> 01:35:39.458
By the Power of Grayskull.

1197
01:35:39.916 --> 01:35:41.208
I...

1198
01:35:41.708 --> 01:35:42.958
have...

1199
01:35:43.458 --> 01:35:46.750
the Power!

1200
01:35:59.083 --> 01:36:01.416
Was that right?
Did I mess up the words?

1201
01:36:01.583 --> 01:36:03.416
No. those are the words.

1202
01:36:03.541 --> 01:36:05.666
Once more with feeling.
perhaps?

1203
01:36:06.000 --> 01:36:07.666
Don't test me. woman.

1204
01:36:11.666 --> 01:36:13.333
Why isn't it working?

1205
01:36:16.041 --> 01:36:17.625
Wait!

1206
01:36:17.750 --> 01:36:20.166
Tell me why it isn't working.

1207
01:36:20.875 --> 01:36:23.333
There's a ritual
I can perform.

1208
01:36:24.833 --> 01:36:27.041
If we return the Sword
to Grayskull.

1209
01:36:27.791 --> 01:36:30.958
to its altar.
I promise you it will work.

1210
01:36:31.083 --> 01:36:35.333
It had better.

1211
01:36:37.541 --> 01:36:39.208
Prepare my ship.

1212
01:36:55.541 --> 01:36:56.750
Hey. lad.

1213
01:36:57.791 --> 01:36:59.000
you want to talk?

1214
01:37:09.625 --> 01:37:12.000
Adam. I'm not
very good with. um.

1215
01:37:13.583 --> 01:37:16.916
talking. You know.
about. uh. what's. you know...

1216
01:37:18.041 --> 01:37:20.041
you know. uh.
what's going on inside.

1217
01:37:20.166 --> 01:37:21.250
You know. the. uh...

1218
01:37:22.750 --> 01:37:25.125
-Feelings?
-Yeah. That.

1219
01:37:26.041 --> 01:37:27.958
But here's what I do know.

1220
01:37:28.500 --> 01:37:31.041
I know how it feels to fail.

1221
01:37:31.208 --> 01:37:35.166
To find out that you are not
who you thought you were.

1222
01:37:48.500 --> 01:37:49.708
It's better she thinks of me

1223
01:37:49.833 --> 01:37:51.416
as an old drunk
who's worth saving

1224
01:37:52.000 --> 01:37:53.833
than an old man
who's worth nothing.

1225
01:37:55.791 --> 01:37:57.125
I failed her.

1226
01:38:03.958 --> 01:38:05.666
I failed you. Adam.

1227
01:38:09.291 --> 01:38:13.500
I promised that I would
protect all of you. And...

1228
01:38:15.708 --> 01:38:17.208
And I couldn't.

1229
01:38:30.875 --> 01:38:32.708
Wow.

1230
01:38:38.250 --> 01:38:40.166
Do you remember what
you used to tell me when...

1231
01:38:40.291 --> 01:38:44.291
I'd get
my ass beat as a kid?

1232
01:38:44.416 --> 01:38:48.375
Yeah. I used
to say. "Drop and give me 20."

1233
01:38:48.541 --> 01:38:51.750
No. You used to say...

1234
01:38:55.666 --> 01:38:57.333
"You got to get back up...

1235
01:38:59.041 --> 01:39:00.458
"and stand tall."

1236
01:39:07.500 --> 01:39:09.583
Maybe we should
both try together.

1237
01:39:11.708 --> 01:39:13.000
What do you say?

1238
01:39:14.583 --> 01:39:15.916
I'd like that.

1239
01:39:26.500 --> 01:39:27.500
Hi.

1240
01:39:28.375 --> 01:39:30.000
I brought someone here
to see you.

1241
01:39:30.458 --> 01:39:31.833
Hmm?

1242
01:39:35.083 --> 01:39:36.375
Cringer?

1243
01:39:37.250 --> 01:39:38.250
Oh. my God.

1244
01:39:38.375 --> 01:39:41.083
Is it okay if I lick you now?

1245
01:39:41.208 --> 01:39:43.083
Uh. yeah. sure.

1246
01:39:43.541 --> 01:39:45.083
Oh. wow.

1247
01:39:46.500 --> 01:39:48.750
I missed you. buddy.

1248
01:39:48.916 --> 01:39:51.250
I can't believe you're here.

1249
01:39:51.416 --> 01:39:52.666
I can't believe
we're all here.

1250
01:39:54.083 --> 01:39:55.625
All the Heroes of Eternia.

1251
01:40:01.000 --> 01:40:03.750
Adam. are you okay?

1252
01:40:05.583 --> 01:40:07.958
Yeah. I think I am.

1253
01:40:08.333 --> 01:40:10.375
Gather round. Come on.

1254
01:40:10.500 --> 01:40:11.875
Gather round for the war room.

1255
01:40:12.041 --> 01:40:14.583
Not a war room.
just a seminar. Seminar.

1256
01:40:14.750 --> 01:40:17.250
Okay. Gather in
for the war seminar. Come on!

1257
01:40:17.416 --> 01:40:19.583
If I could just have
your attention. please.

1258
01:40:19.875 --> 01:40:21.958
I... I'd just like
to take a moment

1259
01:40:22.083 --> 01:40:24.875
to ideate on
an escape strategy.

1260
01:40:25.000 --> 01:40:26.541
A what?

1261
01:40:26.708 --> 01:40:28.333
Is this supposed
to be a battle speech?

1262
01:40:28.500 --> 01:40:30.791
Team building.
Yeah. Team building.

1263
01:40:30.958 --> 01:40:32.708
-Who is this guy?
-Yeah. Who are you?

1264
01:40:33.250 --> 01:40:34.541
I'm Adam. Prince of Eternia.

1265
01:40:34.708 --> 01:40:36.750
Uh. excuse me. Hi.

1266
01:40:36.916 --> 01:40:39.125
Yeah. I thought Adam was dead.

1267
01:40:39.291 --> 01:40:41.000
Hey. Put your neck away.
Let him talk.

1268
01:40:41.166 --> 01:40:42.583
Uh. no.
Not dead.

1269
01:40:43.041 --> 01:40:45.250
As you can see.
very much alive.

1270
01:40:45.416 --> 01:40:47.208
- What did he say?
- Speak up. We can't hear you.

1271
01:40:47.375 --> 01:40:49.916
Okay. Sorry. So when...
when I was on Earth.

1272
01:40:50.750 --> 01:40:53.291
I learned
that success in the workplace

1273
01:40:53.416 --> 01:40:55.416
doesn't come down to one man.

1274
01:40:55.583 --> 01:40:58.000
or woman.

1275
01:40:58.166 --> 01:40:59.750
or whatever that is.

1276
01:40:59.916 --> 01:41:01.541
Person. You know?

1277
01:41:01.708 --> 01:41:04.583
It comes down to many people
working together.

1278
01:41:04.750 --> 01:41:06.791
-Workplace?
-We're in a dungeon.

1279
01:41:06.958 --> 01:41:09.625
No. I know that. Um...

1280
01:41:11.750 --> 01:41:16.875
Look. I know most of you
don't know me.

1281
01:41:19.208 --> 01:41:20.708
But I know all of you.

1282
01:41:23.250 --> 01:41:24.250
Mekaneck.

1283
01:41:25.708 --> 01:41:29.083
Heroic human periscope.

1284
01:41:30.416 --> 01:41:31.416
And Ram Man.

1285
01:41:32.166 --> 01:41:33.208
You ram!

1286
01:41:34.375 --> 01:41:35.375
And you're a man.

1287
01:41:35.666 --> 01:41:37.000
Hell yeah. I do.

1288
01:41:37.125 --> 01:41:39.958
And you. Fisto!
You fist people!

1289
01:41:40.083 --> 01:41:41.083
Yes. I do!

1290
01:41:43.791 --> 01:41:44.875
And Dian.

1291
01:41:47.250 --> 01:41:49.916
You pushed me into the lockers
when I was a kid. so...

1292
01:41:51.541 --> 01:41:52.541
Hell yeah. I did.

1293
01:41:52.708 --> 01:41:53.916
I know all of you.

1294
01:41:55.500 --> 01:41:57.333
I kept you close to my heart.

1295
01:41:58.125 --> 01:42:00.250
Eternia. It's a part of me.

1296
01:42:00.916 --> 01:42:03.416
