What matters is what you do.

1563
02:02:56.083 --> 02:02:59.750
So do something right.

1564
02:03:07.000 --> 02:03:08.000
Hmm.

1565
02:03:21.250 --> 02:03:23.208
Oh. you... you boob.

1566
02:03:23.375 --> 02:03:25.958
You muscle-bound milquetoast.

1567
02:03:26.125 --> 02:03:29.041
There is no right
that will be done here.

1568
02:03:29.208 --> 02:03:32.791
There is no good in me
that you might uncover.

1569
02:03:33.458 --> 02:03:36.750
There is nothing you can say
that will change my nature.

1570
02:03:36.916 --> 02:03:40.250
for I... I am...

1571
02:03:42.750 --> 02:03:44.083
a villain.

1572
02:03:47.541 --> 02:03:50.916
And...
does it feel good.

1573
02:04:18.916 --> 02:04:19.916
Look at you.

1574
02:04:20.083 --> 02:04:22.041
A feeble. worthless child.

1575
02:04:22.791 --> 02:04:24.750
Oh. yes.
you may have the Power.

1576
02:04:24.875 --> 02:04:27.166
but you're too scared
to use it.

1577
02:04:27.625 --> 02:04:31.125
And you don't even know how.

1578
02:04:32.208 --> 02:04:33.750
I know how to use it.

1579
02:04:38.083 --> 02:04:39.458
I just prefer not to.

1580
02:04:45.958 --> 02:04:47.083
Huh?

1581
02:05:04.291 --> 02:05:07.208
Is that...
Is that all you've got?

1582
02:05:07.625 --> 02:05:09.500
I was pulling my punches.

1583
02:05:47.166 --> 02:05:49.833
Do you want to talk?

1584
02:05:50.000 --> 02:05:51.958
Okay. What do you
want to talk about?

1585
02:05:52.708 --> 02:05:54.708
The time for talk is over.

1586
02:06:31.791 --> 02:06:32.791
Get up. squink.

1587
02:06:43.541 --> 02:06:44.708
There you are.

1588
02:06:46.416 --> 02:06:47.500
Thanks.

1589
02:07:46.500 --> 02:07:48.416
So that was nice. the way
you took that guy and

1590
02:07:48.541 --> 02:07:49.625
- I squeezed his hand and...
- Yeah.

1591
02:07:49.750 --> 02:07:51.916
- So. what do you think?
- We killed all of them.

1592
02:07:52.083 --> 02:07:53.083
- Ah.
- Oh. wow!

1593
02:07:53.250 --> 02:07:54.833
This is
a little revealing.

1594
02:08:14.125 --> 02:08:15.250
Hey. Adam.

1595
02:08:15.416 --> 02:08:16.416
Hey.

1596
02:08:17.500 --> 02:08:20.375
How's it going with your.
uh...

1597
02:08:22.083 --> 02:08:23.583
your feelings and such?

1598
02:08:25.708 --> 02:08:26.916
Good. Good. Yeah.

1599
02:08:27.250 --> 02:08:28.666
I want you to know.

1600
02:08:29.083 --> 02:08:30.958
if you ever want to talk.

1601
02:08:32.041 --> 02:08:33.083
I'm here.

1602
02:08:34.500 --> 02:08:35.500
Great.

1603
02:08:37.166 --> 02:08:39.416
Or if you want to arm wrestle.

1604
02:08:40.875 --> 02:08:42.500
Or you want me
to beat you with a stick.

1605
02:08:42.625 --> 02:08:45.875
- I'm also here. All right?
- Oh.

1606
02:08:46.583 --> 02:08:47.666
Likewise.

1607
02:08:49.416 --> 02:08:50.958
Eternia's finest.

1608
02:08:54.666 --> 02:08:55.791
Look at them.

1609
02:08:55.958 --> 02:08:58.291
All the heroes
you drew from your childhood.

1610
02:08:59.083 --> 02:09:00.208
Ram Man.

1611
02:09:00.875 --> 02:09:02.000
Fisto.

1612
02:09:02.166 --> 02:09:04.458
and what did you call
that guy again?

1613
02:09:05.125 --> 02:09:06.583
- Oh. it's Mekaneck.
- Right.

1614
02:09:06.708 --> 02:09:08.625
-Annoying.
-Yeah.

1615
02:09:11.541 --> 02:09:13.041
Did you ever have
a name for me?

1616
02:09:20.250 --> 02:09:23.750
Uh. Warrior Goddess.

1617
02:09:25.125 --> 02:09:26.291
-Oh.
-Because... Well. because

1618
02:09:26.416 --> 02:09:27.916
I was just a kid. so...

1619
02:09:28.041 --> 02:09:29.208
- Yeah. like. it's strong.
- Wow. That's...

1620
02:09:29.333 --> 02:09:30.500
That's great.

1621
02:09:30.625 --> 02:09:31.833
I wouldn't look too much
into it. I...

1622
02:09:31.958 --> 02:09:33.291
You had a name
for yourself. too. didn't you?

1623
02:09:33.458 --> 02:09:35.583
- No. No.
- Yeah. you did. Come on.

1624
02:09:35.750 --> 02:09:36.791
Tell us.

1625
02:09:37.166 --> 02:09:38.166
You're going to laugh.

1626
02:09:38.375 --> 02:09:39.583
Probably. but tell us.

1627
02:09:39.750 --> 02:09:40.750
What is it?

1628
02:09:43.375 --> 02:09:44.375
He-Man.

1629
02:09:45.291 --> 02:09:46.291
What?

1630
02:09:46.916 --> 02:09:47.916
He-Man.

1631
02:09:48.083 --> 02:09:49.333
That's worse than I
thought it was going to be.

1632
02:09:49.458 --> 02:09:50.625
-Isn't that redundant?
-What does it mean?

1633
02:09:50.750 --> 02:09:52.750
It's like a...
like a strong man.

1634
02:09:52.875 --> 02:09:54.916
Like a...
Like a masculine fellow.

1635
02:09:55.041 --> 02:09:56.041
Yeah.

1636
02:09:56.541 --> 02:09:58.208
-What? It's too macho?
-No. No.

1637
02:09:58.333 --> 02:09:59.458
Wow.
that's very manly.

1638
02:09:59.583 --> 02:10:00.916
And you are very manly.

1639
02:10:01.041 --> 02:10:02.041
It's clever.

1640
02:10:02.958 --> 02:10:03.958
Yo. what do you think?

1641
02:10:05.666 --> 02:10:08.625
Uh. yeah.
Yeah. man. this is...

1642
02:10:10.375 --> 02:10:11.375
cool.

1643
02:10:11.541 --> 02:10:12.958
Like. it's cool to see
that it was all real

1644
02:10:13.083 --> 02:10:14.375
and I wasn't a crazy person.

1645
02:10:14.541 --> 02:10:15.708
Yeah. you know.

1646
02:10:15.833 --> 02:10:17.375
now I'm standing
next to a green tiger.

1647
02:10:17.500 --> 02:10:19.375
It's like
who would have thought.

1648
02:10:19.791 --> 02:10:21.625
But. hey. thank you for

1649
02:10:21.791 --> 02:10:26.125
coming to get me
to prove it was all real.

1650
02:10:26.291 --> 02:10:27.833
Oh.
my red light's blinking.

1651
02:10:28.000 --> 02:10:30.916
I'm getting a distress signal
from an Avion village.

1652
02:10:31.083 --> 02:10:33.291
Sounds like a job for He-Man.

1653
02:10:33.458 --> 02:10:35.166
He-Man.

1654
02:10:37.583 --> 02:10:41.791
Yes. I am going to go
and do that thing. See...

1655
02:10:42.291 --> 02:10:43.791
Over there. So...

1656
02:10:46.208 --> 02:10:47.875
Cringer.

1657
02:10:48.000 --> 02:10:50.125
Do we have to?

1658
02:10:56.666 --> 02:10:59.250
Is he running off
to change in secret again?

1659
02:10:59.416 --> 02:11:00.416
Yep.

1660
02:11:00.583 --> 02:11:04.666
Does he think we all forgot?
Pretty much everyone knows.

1661
02:11:05.125 --> 02:11:07.291
I mean. we could just look
the other direction.

1662
02:11:07.416 --> 02:11:09.291
if that's easier?

1663
02:11:09.958 --> 02:11:13.166
Nah. let him do his thing.

1664
02:11:52.125 --> 02:11:53.750
In today's story.

1665
02:11:53.875 --> 02:11:57.125
we saw that muscles
don't necessarily make a man.

1666
02:11:57.291 --> 02:11:59.916
And that having
a skull for a face

1667
02:12:00.041 --> 02:12:01.541
pretty much guarantees

1668
02:12:01.708 --> 02:12:03.750
you're the bad guy.

1669
02:12:03.916 --> 02:12:05.666
Until next time.

1670
02:14:32.291 --> 02:14:33.666
I had given up hope.

1671
02:14:35.333 --> 02:14:36.583
Of both of them.

1672
02:14:41.333 --> 02:14:44.250
Well. perhaps one day
she'll come back to us. too.

1673
02:15:07.625 --> 02:15:09.541
Force Captain Adora?

1674
02:15:09.708 --> 02:15:10.708
No.

1675
02:15:12.500 --> 02:15:13.916
Not anymore.

1676
02:20:02.500 --> 02:20:05.291
I must say.
you've looked better.
